=== Bicep Review: 1-1-basic-rag-default ===
Date: 2025-07-15

[CRITICAL] issues (deployment will fail):
- foundry.bicep: Foundry Project uses wrong resource type `Microsoft.CognitiveServices/accounts@2024-10-01` with `kind: 'AIServices'`. Should be `Microsoft.CognitiveServices/accounts/projects` (child resource under Foundry account). Current code creates two separate standalone AI Services accounts instead of a Foundry Hub + Project hierarchy. The portal will not recognize this as a Foundry Project.
- foundry.bicep: `projectName = 'my-rag-chatbot'` is a static string without `uniqueString()`. Since `customSubDomainName: projectName` requires global uniqueness, deployment will fail if the subdomain 'my-rag-chatbot' is already taken by any other Azure tenant.

[WARNING] issues (may cause problems):
- foundry.bicep: Comment on line 11 mentions `allowProjectManagement: true` is required, but this property is not set in the Foundry account's properties block. If using the correct `accounts/projects` child resource type, this property may be needed on the parent account.
- main.bicep: No role assignments defined — Foundry, Search, Storage, Key Vault have SystemAssigned identities but no RBAC roles are granted between services (e.g., Foundry → Storage Blob Data Contributor, Foundry → Search Index Data Contributor). Services won't be able to access each other without manual RBAC setup.

[INFO] suggestions (nice to have):
- All resource names (except projectName) correctly use `uniqueString(resourceGroup().id)` for global uniqueness.
- Storage properly configured: `isHnsEnabled: true` (ADLS Gen2), `allowBlobPublicAccess: false`, `minimumTlsVersion: 'TLS1_2'`.
- Key Vault: `enablePurgeProtection: true`, `enableRbacAuthorization: true` — good security defaults.
- Model deployments have sequential dependency via `dependsOn` — prevents race conditions.
- `.bicepparam` uses correct `using` syntax with no sensitive values.
- No `@secure()` misuse detected. No hardcoded secrets.
- API versions are recent and valid (CognitiveServices 2024-10-01, KeyVault 2024-04-01-preview, Search 2024-06-01-preview, Storage 2024-01-01).
- Module references use correct relative paths and parameter pass-through.

Overall: FAIL
